		&lt;li&gt;Development of high-level programming languages such as C and C++.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Smaller, faster, and more reliable than earlier generations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Introduction of operating systems that allowed multiple applications to run simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advantages:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Reduced size and cost due to integrated circuit technology.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Enhanced computational speed and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Improved reliability and lower power consumption.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important Points:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Third-generation computers paved the way for the development of personal computers in later generations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They were widely used in business, education, and scientific research due to their versatility.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The transition to integrated circuits marked a significant milestone in computer technology.&lt;/li&gt;
