&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fiber optics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span align-items:=&quot;&quot; display:=&quot;&quot; gap:=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fiber optics&lt;/strong&gt; technology uses light to transmit data over long distances, providing high-speed internet and communication services.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It offers &lt;strong&gt;higher bandwidth&lt;/strong&gt; compared to traditional copper cables, which makes it suitable for WAN (Wide Area Network) connections.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fiber optics are less susceptible to electromagnetic interference, ensuring &lt;strong&gt;stable and reliable connections&lt;/strong&gt; over long distances.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;They are widely used in &lt;strong&gt;telecommunications, internet services, and data center connections&lt;/strong&gt; due to their efficiency and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span align-items:=&quot;&quot; display:=&quot;&quot; gap:=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ethernet&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ethernet is a technology commonly used for local area networks (LANs).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It provides high-speed data transfer within a limited geographical area, such as within a building or campus.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ethernet cables are typically used for short-distance communication, making them less suitable for WAN connections.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bluetooth&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Bluetooth is a wireless technology used for short-range communication between devices.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is commonly used for connecting peripherals like headphones, keyboards, and mice to computers and smartphones.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Bluetooth is not suitable for establishing WAN connections due to its limited range and lower data transfer speeds.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wi-Fi&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Wi-Fi is a wireless networking technology that allows devices to connect to the internet within a limited area, such as a home or office.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It uses radio waves to provide high-speed internet access, but its range is limited compared to fiber optics.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Wi-Fi is commonly used for local area networks (LANs) rather than wide area networks (WANs).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fiber optics&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Fiber optics use light signals to transmit data over long distances, providing higher bandwidth and faster speeds.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They are ideal for WAN connections, as they can cover extensive geographical areas with minimal signal loss.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Fiber optics are less affected by electromagnetic interference, ensuring stable and reliable communication.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This technology is widely used in telecommunications, internet services, and data centers for efficient data transmission.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
